In the first code snippet, you just return the http response code, but no zip file in the body. [You can pass the body either as argument to the ok method or by using the explicit body() method.][1]

So, either:

    zipOutputStream.close();
    return ResponseEntity
             .ok()
             .body(zipOutputStream);

or:

    zipOutputStream.close();
    return ResponseEntity
             .ok(zipOutputStream);

like in [these examples][2] 

In the second code snippet, you pass a lambda expression to the body() method. This does not work imho, because the lambda expression does not deliver a result value. As above, try passing the instance of the zipfile explicitly to the body() method.

Additionally, you must forward the zipOutputStream to the response outputStream, like this answer [suggests.][3]  The whole code would then look like this:

    	@RequestMapping(value=&quot;/downloadQuestion&quot;, produces=&quot;application/zip&quot;, method = { RequestMethod.GET, RequestMethod.POST })
	public ResponseEntity&lt;?&gt; zipFiles(@AuthenticationPrincipal CustomUserDetails user, @RequestParam(&quot;fileList&quot;) String[] fileList, @RequestParam(&quot;assnname&quot;) String assnname, @RequestParam(&quot;question&quot;) String question, HttpServletResponse response) {
		try {
			var zipOutputStream = new ZipOutputStream(response.getOutputStream());

			ArrayList&lt;File&gt; files = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();

			String questionDirectory = user.getDirectorypath()+&quot;/&quot;+assnname+&quot;/&quot;+question;


			for (String s : fileList) {
				files.add(new File(questionDirectory + &quot;/&quot; + s));
			}

			for (File file : files) {

				zipOutputStream.putNextEntry(new ZipEntry(file.getName()));
				FileInputStream fileInputStream = new FileInputStream(file);

				IOUtils.copy(fileInputStream, zipOutputStream);

				fileInputStream.close();
				zipOutputStream.closeEntry();
			}

			zipOutputStream.finish();
			zipOutputStream.close();

			return ResponseEntity
					.ok()
					.header(&quot;Content-Disposition&quot;, &quot;attachment; filename=\&quot;&quot; + assnname + &quot;.zip\&quot;&quot;)
					.body(zipOutputStream);
		}
		catch (IOException ioe) {
			return ResponseEntity.internalServerError()
					.body(&quot;Could not generate zip file&quot;);
		}
	}


